Package io.github.isotes.net.tun.io

Class Packet

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.isotes.net.tun.io.Packet
  • public final class Packet
extends Object
    The packet abstraction used for the primary I/O functions of TunDevice.

    The main attribute for manipulation is the packet ByteBuffer. Additionally, the class contains a small set of utility functions. The uint* functions take the ByteBuffer.order() into account, which defaults to the network byte order (big endian) when obtained from one of the TunDevice.read() methods. The utility methods do not change (or save and restore) the Buffer.position() of packet.

    There are no limitations on manipulating a Packet obtained from one of the TunDevice.read() functions.
